    <item>
      <title>Code</title>
      <link>http://clukewatson.github.io/code/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://clukewatson.github.io/code/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;matlab&#34;&gt;Matlab&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GMM in Matlab&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Blurb:&lt;/em&gt; this file explains how to perform General Method of Moments in Matlab and calculate White SEs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Main file: &lt;a href=&#34;http://clukewatson.github.io/files/code/matlab/gmm.m&#34;&gt;gmm.m&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GMM objective: &lt;a href=&#34;http://clukewatson.github.io/files/code/matlab/gmm_obj.m&#34;&gt;gmm_obj.m&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Windmeijer (2019) First-Stage Weighted GMM&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;em&gt;Blurb:&lt;/em&gt; this two-step procedure uses the residuals from a linear projection of endogenous variable on the instruments to weights the GMM moments &lt;span  class=&#34;math&#34;&gt;\( E[Z^{\prime} u] \)&lt;/span&gt;, allowing for clustering.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Main file: &lt;a href=&#34;http://clukewatson.github.io/files/code/matlab/W_gmm_cluster.m&#34;&gt;W_gmm_cluster.m&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BLP (1995) IGMM in Matlab&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;http://clukewatson.github.io/mycode/blp_igmm/&#34;&gt;BLP_IGMM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;r--rmarkdown&#34;&gt;R + Rmarkdown&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Blurb:&lt;/em&gt; this provides a template for using Rmarkdown; assumes necessary packages installed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rmd file: &lt;a href=&#34;http://clukewatson.github.io/files/code/r/markdown/howdy.Rmd&#34;&gt;howdy.Rmd&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PDF output: &lt;a href=&#34;http://clukewatson.github.io/files/code/r/markdown/howdy.pdf&#34;&gt;howdy.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Blurb:&lt;/em&gt; this creates plots for Year to Date JOE ads for US Full Time Academic jobs by REPEC Top 10 and Top 25 US Econ dept institutions&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;E.g., MIT Mgmt is &amp;quot;Top 10&amp;quot; because MIT Econ is Top 10&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;R file: &lt;a href=&#34;http://clukewatson.github.io/files/code/r/joe_usft_academic.R&#34;&gt;joe_usft_academic.R&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;julia&#34;&gt;Julia&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/clukewatson/juptyernotebooks/blob/master/ec821b_hw3_pt1.ipynb&#34;&gt;Simulating Multivariate Normal Probabilities&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/clukewatson/juptyernotebooks/blob/master/ec821b_hw3_pt2.ipynb&#34;&gt;Probit MLE; Probit Simulated MLE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
